e`, and the four URL fields. An index can alternatively contain a single `not-for-native-image: true` marker with a reason. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:165:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:169:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:177:    LoadIndex --> Tested{\"Any entry with<br/><code>v ∈ tested-versions</code>?\"}\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:178:    Tested -- yes --> UseTested[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:180:    DefaultFor -- yes --> UseDefault[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:184:    Latest -- yes --> UseLatest[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:206:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:216:- **FR-T-6** Newly added `tested-versions` entries are recorded in `index.json` only after they pass on **every** required environment (enforced by `verify-new-library-version-compatibility`).\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsSupport.java:99:            throw new GradleExc